# Cursor Rules Index

## Overview
This directory follows a MECE (Mutually Exclusive, Collectively Exhaustive) structure to make rules discoverable and scoped by concern. High-level categories are: general, languages, stacks, frameworks, topics, and packages.

## Global vs Project-Specific Rules

**This repository contains global rules** that apply across all projects. These rules cover:

- General patterns and standards
- Language-specific conventions (TypeScript, Python)
- Framework standards (Next.js, FastAPI, React Native)
- Cross-cutting topics (API design, Git workflow, security, quality)
- Testing and accessibility standards

**Project-specific rules** should remain in their respective projects (e.g., `my-project/.cursor/rules/`) and should:

- Reference global rules where applicable
- Focus on project-specific patterns and business logic
- Avoid duplicating global standards

**How it works**: Cursor IDE automatically discovers rules in parent directories. When this repository is in your workspace path, Cursor will apply these global rules alongside project-specific rules (project rules take precedence for conflicts).

For architecture details, see `plans/cursor/architecture.md`.

