## Usage Guidelines
- Read relevant rules in your scope before work
- Follow standards; propose edits when reality changes
- Prefer linking to detailed docs in `/docs/`
- **For projects**: Reference global rules, don't duplicate them. Keep only project-specific patterns.

## Notes
- Testing standards: If we own it or write it, we test it directly - no mocking. Only external third-party services can be mocked. See `frameworks/testing/standards.mdc`.
- All general rules have `alwaysApply: true` and will be applied to all projects.
- Framework, language, and stack-specific rules have appropriate globs and will apply when matching files are present.
- **Architecture**: Global rules (this repo) + Project-specific rules (in each project) = Complete rule set